                  <interp inst="t18070701-99-crimeloc602" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18070701-99-off600 t18070701-99-crimeloc602"></join>. On the 2nd of July, a quarter past seven in the morning, I hung the pantaloons on the shop door within the shop; I missed them between six and seven in the afternoon. From information I pursued after the prisoner, I found him at Mr. Windsor's shop, Whitechapel; he was offering the pantaloons to pledge, I laid hold of him, I said they were the pantaloons that hung in our shop, and he had just stolen them; he said they were his. I know them to be my mistresses' property, they have our shop mark.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I am subject to fits, these breeches belong to me, they never belonged to that young man.</p>
               <p>
